               <head>Miscellany, prose and poetry</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary />
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100084 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100087 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85060956 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85018984" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4072-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Alternative title written in English on octagonal label on front flap: Majmooa dast(a)wezat wo gazal aur noskhezat wogaira</p>
                        <p>Untitled and unattributed triglot miscellany or notebook in Persian, Urdu, and Sanskrit</p>
                        <p>Comprising excerpts from varied poetic compositions by the author and others (Persian and Urdu); numerological tables; recipes for food and medicine; Devanagari alphabet with pronunciation in Persian; Sanskrit prayer to the deity Ganesh; transcripts of older and contemporaneous letters; accounts; chronograms for contemporary events; titles of nobles and British East India Company officers; designs for seals; ciphers; horoscopes</p>
                        <p>Includes several dated inscriptions, ranging from 1820-40s, with reoccuring mention of Farrukhabad, Munshi Durga Prashad, and Sa'id al-Din Khan (the nāʾib of the younger nawab), etc.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="urd" xml:lang="per">Persian, Urdu, Sanskrit</textLang>
                     <note>Copied from an original =-=-=-=-</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
